[{'general_issue_code': 'CAW', 'general_issue_code_display': 'Clean Air and Water (quality)', 'description': "1. The Roundtable has encouraged Congressional oversight of such unilateral Executive Branch actions. 
2.  Educating policymakers on the implications of efforts by EPA and the Army Corps of Engineers to unilaterally expand their2. (cont.) regulatory authority under the Clean Water Act.  

3.  Educating policymakers regarding the potential consequences for Western headwater states of the President's unilaterally-instituted National Oceans Policy.  Supported Congressional efforts to limit funding of the Policy's implementation, including support of the Flores amendment to H.R. 152.", 'foreign_entity_issues': '', 'lobbyists': [{'lobbyist': {'id': 6555, 'prefix': 'ms', 'prefix_display': 'MS.', 'first_name': 'HOLLY', 'nickname': None, 'middle_name': 'E', 'last_name': 'PROPST', 'suffix': None, 'suffix_display': None}, 'covered_position': 'U.S. House of Representatives', 'new': False}], 'government_entities': [{'id': 200, 'name': 'Army, Dept of (Corps of Engineers)'}, {'id': 15, 'name': 'Council on Environmental Quality (CEQ)'}, {'id': 33, 'name': 'Energy, Dept of'}, {'id': 49, 'name': 'Environmental Protection Agency (EPA)'}, {'id': 2, 'name': 'HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES'}, {'id': 36, 'name': 'Interior, Dept of (DOI)'}, {'id': 1, 'name': 'SENATE'}]}, {'general_issue_code': 'NAT', 'general_issue_code_display': 'Natural Resources', 'description': "1.
